The remaining nine species can be further divided into two groups based on the presence or absence of dorsal projections on the body. The first group consists of four species, which are dorsally smooth (this includes
O. mayeri Barnard, 1916
;
O. tasmaniensis Guiler, 1954
;
O. pearce Guerra-García, 2006
; and
O. berentsae Takeuchi & Lowry, 2007
). The second group consists of five species, which are equipped with dorsal projections (
O. gordoni Guiler, 1954
;
O. australis ( Haswell, 1880 )
;
O. spinigera Mori, 1996
;
O. nana Guerra-García, 2004
; and
O. tuberculata Guerra-García & Takeuchi, 2004
).
